# Kubernetes Configuration Management

This module handles the management of Kubernetes configurations (`~/.kube/config` file).

## Key Components

### Models
- [KubeConfigModels.swift](mdc:ConfigForge/Models/KubeConfigModels.swift) - Data models for Kubernetes configurations

### Services
- [KubeConfigFileManager.swift](mdc:ConfigForge/Services/KubeConfigFileManager.swift) - Handles reading/writing Kubernetes config files
- [KubeConfigParser.swift](mdc:ConfigForge/Services/KubeConfigParser.swift) - Parses Kubernetes config file format

### Data Flow
1. Kubernetes config is loaded from disk via `KubeConfigFileManager`
2. Raw file content is parsed by `KubeConfigParser` into Kubernetes model objects
3. The `MainViewModel` manages these configurations and user interactions
4. The UI displays different aspects (Contexts, Clusters, Users) based on user selection
5. When changes are made, the configurations are converted back to YAML and saved
